Wow, this game is too beautiful!

@update 
I had to change the review to negative because the game crashing every time after a cutscene. Hope you will fix it soon. Cheers

took much from "Hollow Knight" with no real understanding of how those mechanics should work;
story is inflated from nothing, mechanics are shaky, platforming not interesting, scripted sections are scripted, "boss fights" are confusing,
still pretty, though, so there's that.

Compared to The Blind Forest; 

More weapons 



That's it, it's more of the same, very addictive, very big recommended

Purchased the game on sale because it looked interesting. It definitely was worth it, had I known it'd be that good of a game I'd buy it for regular price;
the ending hurt my soul but other than that 11/10 game




Though, I'd be lying if I said I didn't rage at some parts
